	<!-- ════ FAQ ════ -->
	<section class="faq" data-reveal>
		<div class="w">
			<div class="sec-hd sec-hd-c">
				<span class="sec-tag">FAQ</span>
				<h2>Common questions.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="faq-list">
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Is this opinionated? Can I swap out libraries?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes, it's opinionated - that's the point. But it's your code after you clone it. Swap PostgreSQL for SQL Server, replace Mediator with MediatR, use a different auth provider. The architecture is the value, not any single library.</p></div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Is this production-ready or just a demo?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>Production-ready. It's been used in real applications for 5 years, battle-tested by thousands of developers. The patterns (CQRS, modular monolith, VSA) are proven at scale. But do your own security review - as with any framework.</p></div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Can I remove modules I don't need?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>Absolutely. Modules are independent bounded contexts. Don't need Auditing? Remove the project reference and the module registration line. The architecture is designed for this.</p></div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>How does this compare to Clean Architecture templates?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>fullstackhero uses Vertical Slice Architecture inside a Modular Monolith - not traditional Clean Architecture layers. You get feature cohesion (everything for a feature in one folder) instead of layer separation (controllers in one folder, services in another). Both are valid; VSA tends to scale better with team size.</p></div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>What databases are supported?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>PostgreSQL out of the box via Npgsql. Since it's built on EF Core, switching to SQL Server, MySQL, or SQLite requires changing the provider registration and connection string. The rest of the data layer (entities, specifications, migrations) stays the same.</p></div>
				</details>
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary>Is there commercial support?</summary>
					<div class="faq-answer"><p>fullstackhero is open-source and MIT licensed. Community support is available via GitHub Issues and Discussions. For bugs, feature requests, or questions - open an issue on GitHub.</p></div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

